🧠 Difference between AI, ML, and DL
🤖 Artificial Intelligence (AI)

👉 The big umbrella

Goal: Make machines behave intelligently like humans
Includes:
Rule-based systems
Machine Learning
Robotics, NLP, etc.

📌 Example:

Chatbots
Self-driving cars
Game-playing AI
📊 Machine Learning (ML)

👉 Subset of AI

Machines learn from data instead of being explicitly programmed
Uses algorithms to find patterns

📌 Example:

Spam email detection
Netflix recommendations
Stock prediction
🧠 Deep Learning (DL)

👉 Subset of ML

Uses neural networks (like brain)
Works best with large data

📌 Example:

Face recognition
Voice assistants (Siri, Alexa)
Self-driving vision systems
